      "text": "\nFirst, common business humor aside, if you have too much to do, meaning you've committed to doing something you don't really have the time and resources to do, then you're in trouble, and something's got to give.  It's a situation everyone gets into sometime (unexpected loss of resources or addition of required functionality), but it shouldn't be business as usual.  See [[Death March]].",
      "id": "15b3dd16cfc1d35511d83ce51221e2af"
