      "text": "<i>The purpose of this note (obviously not successfully communicated) is to point out that when we feel we have too little time, or too much to do, we must reduce scope.  As developers, we have control over \"hidden scope\", the things we do just because we think they're necessary.  Some of them may not be, and by reducing or getting rid of them, we can get more done by doing less of what isn't needed.--[[Ron Jeffries]]</i>",
